 in the New York State Legislature. He died at Dover Furnace in March 1853 at age sixty-five."}],"slug":"william-hooker-1788"},"H01473":{"id":"H01473","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":7,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":2},"parents":{"mother_id":"H00429","father_id":"H00553"},"tags":["cousin_marriage","double_hooker_ancestry","extraordinary_longevity"],"sources":[{"short":"WikiTree (online genealogy)","url":"https://www.wikitree.com/"},{"short":"Find a Grave — South Dover Rural Cemetery","url":"https://www.findagrave.com/cemetery/1976581/south-dover-rural-cemetery"},{"short":"Stanley Families of America (Warren, 1887?)","page":"entries 444-449"}],"birth":{"year":1790,"month":11,"day":6,"city":"Kensington","state":"Connecticut","county":"Hartford","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1885,"month":4,"day":21,"city":"Dover Furnace","state":"New York","county":"Dutchess","country":"United States"},"marriages":[{"children_ids":["H02791","H02792"],"spouse_id":"H01429","marriage_number":1,"date_year":1814,"date_month":1,"date_day":9,"location_city":"Hartford","location_state":"Connecticut","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1853}],"gender":"male","number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Amelia Stanley Hooker","first_name":"Amelia","last_name":"Stanley","married_names":["Hooker"],"maiden_name":"Stanley"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM240"},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Cousin marriage united two Hooker branches","body":"Amelia carried Hooker blood from both parents — her mother Ann Hooker Stanley descended from Samuel Hooker Jr., her father Seth Stanley descended through his mother Hannah Hart from Abigail Hooker. When she married her cousin Dr. William Hooker in Hartford on January 9, 1814, three Hooker branches converged in their two children — a triple descent that closed a century-and-a-half family loop."}],"former_ids":["HD0539"],"slug":"amelia-stanley-1790"}},"burialCemetery":{"id":"CEM240","primary_name":"South Dover Rural Cemetery","location":{"city":"Wingdale","county":"Dutchess","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"find_a_grave_url":"https://www.findagrave.com/cemetery/1976581/south-dover-rural-cemetery","hooker_connections":["H01429","H01473","H02791","H02792","H04401","H04403","H04405","HD3588","HD3589","HD3590","HD3591","HD3592","HD3593","X01229","X02738","X02739","X02740"],"notes":"Resting place of the South Dover Hooker family across multiple generations: Dr. William Hooker (H01429, 1788-1853) and his cousin Amelia Stanley Hooker (HD0539, 1790-1885), their two children William Jr. (H02791) and Ann Hooker Vincent (H02792), William Jr.'s wife Sarah Varney Cutler Hooker (X01229) and four of their five children, plus Ann's husband Edwin Vincent (X02738) and her three Vincent children — Ella, Amelia H., Charles William — and onward through the Vincent line via Charles Kenneth and his wife Edith Akin Vincent down to Walter Akin Vincent (HD3593, WWII Navy). The 1814 cousin marriage united two Hooker branches via Amelia's TRIPLE Hooker descent.","gps":{"lat":41.65263,"lng":-73.5559}},"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}